        "asset": "/systems/morphous-lilac/motif.png",
        "prompt": "Use case: photorealistic-natural\nAsset type: Morphous Lilac transparent motif chroma-key source\nPrimary request: Create only an isolated lilac panicle botanical motif for a design-system catalog, no environment, no props, no text.\nSubject: A real Syringa vulgaris lilac panicle with unmistakable lilac-purple color: one full conical cluster of many tiny four-petaled blossoms in soft lilac, mauve, and pale violet-purple hues (#a77bc5, #c5a4dc, #d8c4ea), a few darker violet unopened buds, one slender woody-green stem, and two matte heart-shaped leaf-green leaves near the base. It must clearly read as lilac, not lavender spikes, not wisteria, not grayscale flowers, not generic purple flowers.\nComposition/framing: centered complete cutout with generous padding on all sides; show the full panicle tip, stem, and leaves without cropping; elegant nostalgic botanical archive silhouette.\nLighting/mood: clean even studio light preserving visible lilac-purple blossoms, leaf-green foliage, spring-grey petal shadows, and natural botanical detail.\nChroma-key workflow: create the subject on a perfectly flat solid #00ffff cyan chroma-key background for background removal. The background must be one uniform color with no shadows, gradients, texture, reflections, floor plane, or lighting variation. Do not use #00ffff, cyan, teal, or blue-green anywhere in the subject. Remove the key locally with remove_chroma_key.py using auto-key border, soft matte, and despill. The final motif.png is RGBA transparent with transparent corners.\nConstraints: no text, no watermark, no vase, no ribbon, no garden background, no bouquet wrap, no field, no second flower species, no shadow, no contact shadow, no reflection, no monochrome flowers."
