        "asset": "/systems/morphous-yew/motif.png",
        "prompt": "Use case: photorealistic-natural\nAsset type: Morphous transparent motif cutout source\nPrimary request: Create only a yew branch, isolated full subject, no environment, no props, no text.\nSubject: One mature yew branch cutting with several woody bark-brown twigs, dense dark green flat needles arranged in two ranks, and a small cluster of vivid red yew arils. Accurate botanical Taxus-style structure, natural uneven branch silhouette, crisp needle detail, matte bark texture, no flowers, no cones, no extra plants.\nComposition/framing: centered complete branch cutout with generous padding on all sides; do not crop the needles, twig tips, or red arils. Diagonal branch orientation is acceptable, but the whole subject must remain fully inside the frame.\nLighting/mood: clean studio light that preserves deep yew-green needles, red aril highlights, bark-brown twigs, and ancient woodland natural texture.\nTransparent workflow: place the subject on a perfectly flat solid #ff00ff chroma-key background for removal. The background must be one uniform color with no shadows, gradients, texture, reflections, floor plane, or lighting variation. Do not use #ff00ff anywhere in the subject.\nConstraints: no text, no watermark, no props, no woodland landscape, no decorative background, no second branch, no animals, no cast shadow, no contact shadow, no reflection."
